1. Resilient Task Processor (Top Priority)
Problem:

Design a system where:

    Tasks are processed by multiple workers
    Failures are retried
    No duplicate execution
You MUST implement:
    Thread pool
    Retry logic
    Idempotency handling


I designed a multi-threaded task processor using a blocking queue and thread pool,
ensured idempotency using a concurrent store,
and implemented bounded retries with backoff to handle failures safely without duplicate execution



    Tasks are processed by multiple workers -> ExecutorService
    Failures are retried -> Math.Random Exception
    No duplicate execution -> ConcurrentHashmap tracking of tasks
You MUST implement:
    Thread pool -> ExecutorService
    Retry logic -> further retried after backoff sleep(attempt * 1000)
    Idempotency handling-> ConcurrentHashmap tracking of tasks

